config MEMLOG
	tristate "memlog: /dev/memlog LLM context-compaction audit log"
	default n
	help
	  Adds the /dev/memlog character device — a per-uid circular buffer
	  in kernel memory for storing LLM "about-to-be-compacted" context
	  snapshots so they survive process death. Records are opaque
	  (CBOR-encoded by convention; the kernel only validates size).
	  Ring capacity is tunable via sysctl kernel.memlog.ring_size.

	  Writers must be in the "memlog" group (configured via the
	  memlog_gid module parameter) or have CAP_SYS_ADMIN.

	  Readers see only their own uid's records by default;
	  CAP_SYS_ADMIN can request the full ring via ioctl.

	  See Documentation/admin-guide/memlog.rst.

	  If unsure, say N. To build as a module, say M; the module is
	  named memlog.
